# AuraTxt Profiles

Profiles describe how to control thinking mode, strip output tags, and declare capabilities for each model family.

## Quick Reference — Thinking Control

| Vendor | location | disable example |
|--------|----------|-----------------|
| NIM / OpenAI-compat (DeepSeek, GLM, Kimi) | `chat_template_kwargs` | `{"thinking": false}` |
| Qwen3 (thinking variants) | `chat_template_kwargs` | `{"enable_thinking": false}` |
| Gemini Flash 2.5+ | `generationConfig.thinkingConfig` | `{"thinkingBudget": 0}` |
| Gemini Pro | `generationConfig.thinkingConfig` | `{"thinkingBudget": 128}` |
| Gemma 4 (via Gemini API) | `generationConfig.thinkingConfig` | `{"thinkingLevel": "none"}` |

## Adding a New Profile (5 steps)

1. Run `auracfg profile --new` (interactive wizard) **or** copy an existing JSON file.
2. Edit `id`, `match.name_patterns`, `priority`, `adapter_compatibility`.
3. Set `thinking.modes.disable` / `thinking.modes.enable_high` payloads.
4. Run `auracfg profile --validate profiles/{id}.json` to check schema.
5. Run `auracfg profile --probe --provider PROV --model MODEL` to verify at runtime.

